  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `geth  1.4.11-stable`\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04\n#### Problem\n\nI can use geth console to manage stuff. And it's working great.\nBut I'm building an API which using it.\nThe problem is that now I'm using bash scripts which calls geth console. And this way things working really really slow. Is there a faster way? Can I build api on GO to access geth functions?\n\nSo here is the structure I'm using right now. \n1) I created a bash script\n\n``` bash\nsudo geth attach <<EOF\n        web3.fromWei(eth.getBalance(\"$1\"), \"ether\")\nEOF\n```\n\n2) And then I created custom nodejs method which call this bash script and grab the output.\n\n``` javascript\napp.get('/newWallet' , function(request, response) {\n\n\n    var command = \"./newwallet.sh\";\n    var child1 = exec(command);\n    var text = ''\n    child1.stdout.on('data', function(output) {\n      text += output;\n\n    })\n    child1.stderr.on('data', function(errdata) {\n      var dataString = errdata.toString()\n      response.send('error')\n      child1.kill()\n    })\n    child1.on('exit', (code) => {\n      var a = text.indexOf('>');\n      var b = text.lastIndexOf('>');\n      var str = text.substring(a+4,b-2)\n      response.send(a + ' ' + b)\n    });\n});\n```\n",
